<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1436,1675,1988]" box="[199,1348,1820,1844]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
Distribution in 
<collectingCountry box="[370,442,1820,1844]" name="Brazil" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Brazil</collectingCountry>
: North, Central-West and Southeast regions (RR, GO, MG) (
<bibRefCitation author="Truxal" box="[1123,1264,1820,1844]" firstAuthor="Truxal" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="1351 - 1517" refId="ref43884" refString="Truxal, F. S. (1953) A revision of the genus Buenoa (Hemiptera: Notonectidae). University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 35, 1351 - 1517." type="journal article" year="1953">Truxal 1953</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Truxal" box="[1275,1335,1820,1844]" firstAuthor="Truxal" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="3 - 23" refId="ref43917" refString="Truxal, F. S. (1957) The Machris Brazilian Expedition Entomology: general; systematics of the Notonectidae (Hemiptera). Contributions in Science, 12, 3 - 23." type="journal article" year="1957">1957</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1436,1675,1988]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
Comments: 
<bibRefCitation author="Truxal" box="[334,489,1855,1879]" firstAuthor="Truxal" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="1351 - 1517" refId="ref43884" refString="Truxal, F. S. (1953) A revision of the genus Buenoa (Hemiptera: Notonectidae). University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 35, 1351 - 1517." type="journal article" year="1953">Truxal (1953)</bibRefCitation>
associated Ireng River with AM, but this river forms part of the border between 
<collectingCountry name="Brazil" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[235,322,1892,1916]" name="Guyana" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Guyana</collectingCountry>
in the northeast portion of RR. Ireng (= Maú) River is part of the Amazon River Basin, but much before reaching AM it joins the Tacutu (= Itacutu) River, which in its turn joins the Uraricoera River, forming the Branco River.
</paragraph>
